<div class="wrap">
  <div class="brand"><div class="dot">L</div><div><b>Leak</b><span>Warm outreach kit</span></div></div>

  <h1>Your 10 warmest, one personal audit offer.</h1>
  <p class="sub">Ready-to-send messages for the people who already know and trust you. Personal, low-pressure, and built to book a 15-minute call, not to hard-sell. Pick the channel each contact actually uses.</p>

  <div class="flag">
    <b>Read me first.</b> I have written and checked these, but I have not sent anything. Sending outreach in your name is your call to make. To fire them: drop your 10 names in the tracker below, paste the matching message, swap the <span style="background:#fde68a;padding:0 3px;border-radius:3px">purple slots</span> for the real details, and hit send. Two things need your decision before you send, both in the flags note I have left you separately: the <b>price</b> ($999 vs the $1,500 on the site) and whether to add a <b>founding-client sweetener</b> for these first few. I have written both a full-price and a founding-client version so you can choose.
  </div>

  <p class="legend">Swap every slot: <span class="slot">Name</span> their first name, <span class="slot">Café</span> their venue, <span class="slot">personal line</span> one true, specific sentence only you could write (how you know them, last time you spoke, something about their place). That one line is what separates this from spam.</p>

  <!-- EMAIL A -->
  <h2>1 . Email . full price</h2>
  <p class="h2note">Best for contacts you would email anyway. The guarantee is the sweetener, so you never sound like you are discounting.</p>
  <div class="msg">
    <div class="subj"><b>Subject:</b> quick one, <span class="slot">Name</span></div>
    <div class="body">Hey <span class="slot">Name</span>,

<span class="slot">personal line, e.g. "Still thinking about that natural wine you poured me at Café last month."</span>

Quick reason I'm writing. I've just launched Leak. I read a café's last 13 weeks of sales, wages and supplier invoices and find exactly where profit is quietly leaking out. Not the big obvious stuff, the small stuff nobody catches: a supplier creeping prices 8% in steps you never see, a weekend rostered for trade that didn't turn up, food cost drifting off your own normal.

I'm doing a handful of these this month and I'd genuinely love <span class="slot">Café</span> to be one of them. On the sample audit I can send you, the method surfaced $12,400 a year across three fixes, none of it visible on the P&L.

It's $999 flat, and it's backed by a promise: I find at least twice that in opportunities, or you don't pay. So worst case, you get a free read of your own numbers.

Want me to send the one-pager, or easier to grab 15 minutes this week?

Mel</div>
  </div>

  <!-- EMAIL B -->
  <h2>2 . Email . founding client</h2>
  <p class="h2note">If you'd rather trade a first-round audit for a testimonial and a case study. Only use with people whose name would carry weight.</p>
  <div class="msg">
    <div class="subj"><b>Subject:</b> want to try something on <span class="slot">Café</span>?</div>
    <div class="body">Hey <span class="slot">Name</span>,

<span class="slot">personal line</span>

I've just launched Leak, an audit that reads a café's last 13 weeks of numbers and finds exactly where profit is leaking out. Supplier creep, weekend rostering, food cost drift, the quiet stuff that never shows on a P&L.

I'm picking a few founding cafés to run first, and I'd love <span class="slot">Café</span> to be one. Here's the deal: I do the full audit for you <span class="slot">free / at $499</span>, and if it's as useful as I think it'll be, all I ask is a few honest words I can quote and permission to reference it.

No catch, no pitch at the end you can't say no to. Worst case you get a proper read of your numbers and I get a bit sharper.

Up for it? I can start this week.

Mel</div>
  </div>

  <!-- IG DM -->
  <h2>3 . Instagram / Facebook DM</h2>
  <p class="h2note">Shorter, warmer, no subject line. Match the tone you'd normally use with them.</p>
  <div class="msg">
    <div class="top"><b>Direct message</b><span class="tag">~60 words</span></div>
    <div class="body"><span class="slot">Name</span>! <span class="slot">personal line</span>

Quick one. I've just launched Leak, I read a café's last 13 weeks of sales, wages and invoices and find where profit's quietly leaking (supplier creep, over-rostered weekends, that kind of thing). My sample audit surfaced $12k a year in one café.

Doing a few this month and would love <span class="slot">Café</span> to be one. It's backed by a 2x-or-you-don'''t-pay promise. Can I send you the one-pager? x</div>
  </div>

  <!-- SMS -->
  <h2>4 . Text message</h2>
  <p class="h2note">For the ones you have a real phone relationship with. Keep it human.</p>
  <div class="msg">
    <div class="top"><b>SMS</b><span class="tag">~40 words</span></div>
    <div class="body">Hey <span class="slot">Name</span>, it's Mel. <span class="slot">personal line</span> I've just launched Leak, I find exactly where a café's profit is leaking from its own numbers. Doing a few audits this month and want <span class="slot">Café</span> in. Backed by a 2x-or-free promise. Can I send you a one-pager?</div>
  </div>

  <!-- FOLLOW UP -->
  <h2>5 . The follow-up (day 3-4, no reply)</h2>
  <p class="h2note">One nudge only. If nothing after this, leave it warm and move on.</p>
  <div class="msg">
    <div class="body">Hey <span class="slot">Name</span>, no worries if the timing's off. If it helps, here's the one-pager so you've got it: <span class="slot">link</span>. The offer holds while I've got audit spots this month. Either way, hope <span class="slot">Café</span>'s flying. x</div>
  </div>

